00:00:03:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:03:090000.Dialogue: Oh, my God. I love this chicken.

00:00:05:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:05:140000.Dialogue: Oh, you know what they say, best things in life are free.

00:00:10:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:10:170000.Dialogue: Okay, you're right. I eat your food a lot. Now, how about this? You can raid my fridge anytime you want.

00:00:15:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:15:100000.Dialogue: Oh, that's very kind of you. Next time I have a hankering to wash down a D-cell battery with a jar of old pickle juice, I'll come a-knockin'.

00:00:24:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:24:110000.Dialogue: Hey, Raj, you didn't send your RSVP in. I'm suppose to ask you if you're bringing someone to the wedding.

00:00:31:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:31:080000.Dialogue: Well, can you make it soon? There's a battle royale going on over the seating charts. In one corner, Bernadette's mom, in the other three, mine.

00:00:38:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:38:100000.Dialogue: Yeah, I hate wedding receptions. Yeah, I wish the bride and groom would take a cue from Bilbo Baggins. Slip on the ring, disappear, and everyone goes home.

00:00:47:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:47:070000.Dialogue: Mm, you liked Professor Geyser's wedding.

00:00:50:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:50:030000.Dialogue: They had a make-your-own-sundae bar. Oh, that was a night to remember. Do you know, on one trip, I just had a bowl of nuts.

00:00:59:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:59:140000.Dialogue: Anyway, you got to let me know if you have a plus one. Because if not, my mom's trying to sneak in the doctor who sucked the fat out of her neck.

00:01:10:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:10:150000.Dialogue: All right, uh, fine. I'm coming and I'm bringing somebody. Uh, Koothrappali plus one.

00:01:18:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:18:150000.Dialogue: He's bringing me; who are you bringing?

00:01:20:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:20:200000.Dialogue: Wow, what a bunch of Nosey O'Donnells.

00:01:26:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:26:040000.Dialogue: I'm not telling. I'm from Asia, I'm mysterious, deal with it.

00:01:32:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:32:030000.Dialogue: Howard aren't having a make-your-own-sundae bar?

00:01:36:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:36:160000.Dialogue: Well, you should. 50% of marriages end in divorce, but 100% of make-your-own-sundae bars end in happiness.

00:02:14:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:14:190000.Dialogue: Hello, Mummy, Daddy. How are you?

00:02:18:230000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:02:18:230000.Dialogue: Oh, I'm sure you can. Just give it a minute.

00:02:23:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:23:060000.Dialogue: Listen, uh, there's something I want to talk to you about. I wasn't ready until now, but... I think it's time.

00:02:30:230000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:02:30:230000.Dialogue: It's finally happening. You're coming out of the closet, aren't you?

00:02:36:050000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:02:36:050000.Dialogue: We love you, and we accept your alternate lifestyle. Just... keep it to yourself.

00:02:42:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:42:090000.Dialogue: No, I'm not gay. If anything, I'm metrosexual.

00:02:49:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:49:080000.Dialogue: It means I like women as well as their skin-care products.

00:02:53:070000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:02:53:070000.Dialogue: Well, if you're not coming out, why did you call us during the cricket semifinals?

00:02:57:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:57:220000.Dialogue: I'm tired of trying to meet someone, and I think I'd like you to help me find a... a wife.

00:03:06:160000.Speaker: Mrs Koothrappali
00:03:06:160000.Dialogue: And just to clarify... a female wife?

00:03:12:190000.Speaker: Dr Koothrappali
00:03:12:190000.Dialogue: Matchmaking-- very smart move, son. Much better than marrying for love.

00:03:31:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:31:080000.Dialogue: Quantum physics makes me so happy.

00:03:36:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:36:220000.Dialogue: It's like looking at the universe naked.

00:03:50:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:50:120000.Dialogue: Well, I was thinking about Sheldon's little joke the other night about me eating all your food.

00:03:55:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:55:050000.Dialogue: Oh! That was no joke. But...

00:03:58:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:58:060000.Dialogue: I understand your confusion, as I am our group's resident cutup.

00:04:03:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:03:020000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, you are our resident cutup?

00:04:18:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:18:200000.Dialogue: Anyway, I got a little residual check from my commercial, and I thought, hey, how about I get the guys a little thank you to pay them back? So, Sheldon... ta-da!

00:04:28:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:28:140000.Dialogue: A vintage mint-in-box 1975 Mego Star Trek Transporter with real transporter action. Hot darn!

00:04:40:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:40:060000.Dialogue: From Stuart, at the comic book store.

00:04:41:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:41:170000.Dialogue: You went to the comic book store by yourself?

00:04:44:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:44:190000.Dialogue: Yeah. It was fun. I walked in, and two different guys got asthma attacks.

00:04:52:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:52:190000.Dialogue: This calls for an expression of gratitude.

00:04:55:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:55:080000.Dialogue: Ooh, am I about to get a rare Sheldon Cooper hug?

00:04:58:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:58:020000.Dialogue: No, not this time. Then they wouldn't be special. Thanks, Penny.

00:05:03:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:03:170000.Dialogue: You're welcome. Don't worry, I didn't forget about you. Oh... Leonard, I got you... a label-maker!

00:05:23:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:23:010000.Dialogue: Mm. And I got you a transporter, too!

00:05:33:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:33:090000.Dialogue: Look, it was actually designed for my vintage Mr. Spock action figure.

00:05:37:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:37:040000.Dialogue: Oh, that's great! Let's open them up and put him in there.

00:05:45:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:45:210000.Dialogue: Come on. Can't we open one up and take a look?

00:05:49:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:49:210000.Dialogue: Once you open the box, it loses its value.

00:05:52:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:52:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, yeah. My mom gave me the same lecture about my virginity.

00:05:58:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:58:030000.Dialogue: Gotta tell you, it was a lot more fun taking it out and playing with it.

00:06:04:220000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:04:220000.Dialogue: Are you sure you want us here when you meet this woman?

00:06:07:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:07:210000.Dialogue: Oh, yes. In my culture, it's expected to have a chaperone to oversee a first date. Plus, I want to make a good impression, and no offense, but with you guys here, I look like I'm six-two.

00:06:19:200000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:19:200000.Dialogue: The nuns always chaperoned the dances at my high school. They used to make us leave room between us for the Holy Spirit.

00:06:26:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:26:230000.Dialogue: Uh, Hindus do the same thing. Except they leave room for a cow.

00:06:31:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:31:130000.Dialogue: Listen, I love your charming racist humor, but any chance you could not mock my religion while she's here?

00:06:37:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:37:110000.Dialogue: Yesterday, you made fun of me for eating lox.

00:06:39:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:39:160000.Dialogue: It's different, your people don't worship lox.

00:06:41:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:41:160000.Dialogue: Clearly, you've never been to brunch with my cousins.

00:06:45:200000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:06:45:200000.Dialogue: So, arranged marriages-- the parents just decide and then you have to get married?

00:06:49:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:06:49:100000.Dialogue: No, no, I get a say in it. But I'm sure whoever shows up will be better company than the threesome I've been having with Aunt Jemima and Mrs. Butterworth.

00:07:01:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:01:020000.Dialogue: Ah, yes. You must be Lakshmi. Uh, nice to meet you.

00:07:06:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:06:150000.Dialogue: Oh! These are my friends. This is Bernadette.

00:07:38:190000.Speaker: Spock
00:07:38:190000.Dialogue: I need to speak with you.

00:07:44:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:44:190000.Dialogue: The only logical explanation is that this is a dream.

00:07:48:040000.Speaker: Spock
00:07:48:040000.Dialogue: It is not the only logical explanation. For example, you could be hallucinating after being hit on the head by, say, a coconut.

00:07:58:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:58:020000.Dialogue: Was I hit on the head by a coconut?

00:08:01:200000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:01:200000.Dialogue: I am not going to dignify that with a response.

00:08:07:010000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:07:010000.Dialogue: Now to the matter at hand. You need to play with the transporter toy.

00:08:12:060000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:12:060000.Dialogue: Yes. And to open it would destroy its value. But remember, like me,

00:08:18:110000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:18:110000.Dialogue: you also have a human half.

00:08:20:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:20:130000.Dialogue: Well, I'm not going to dignify that with a response.

00:08:26:220000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:26:220000.Dialogue: What is the purpose of a toy?

00:08:30:050000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:30:050000.Dialogue: Therefore, to not play with it would be...?

00:08:33:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:33:050000.Dialogue: Illogical. Damn it, Spock, you're right.

00:08:43:030000.Speaker: Spock
00:08:43:030000.Dialogue: You have to wake up first.

00:08:44:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:44:180000.Dialogue: Oh, of course. Set phasers to dumb, right?

00:08:55:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:55:040000.Dialogue: This is wrong, this is wrong. I'm so excited, but this is wrong.

00:09:02:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:02:020000.Dialogue: I'm going to do it. I'm doing it. I did it.

00:09:12:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:12:050000.Dialogue: That's what I always thought 1975 smelled like.

00:09:18:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:18:040000.Dialogue: One to beam down, Mr. Scott. Aye, aye, Mr. Spock. Energize.

00:09:40:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:40:090000.Dialogue: No. No. Don't be broken. Oh, please, don't be broken. What did you make me do?!

00:10:13:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:13:190000.Dialogue: Well, I hope you saved room for chocolate lava cake.

00:10:17:150000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:17:150000.Dialogue: Impressive. What goes into making something like that?

00:10:21:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:21:150000.Dialogue: Well, you start out by trying to make chocolate soufflé, and when it falls, you panic, quickly change the name, and voila, lava cake.

00:10:30:130000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:30:130000.Dialogue: I bet our parents are dying to know how things are going here.

00:10:33:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:33:140000.Dialogue: Well, let's see. Yep, three missed calls.

00:10:38:170000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:38:170000.Dialogue: Four missed calls, two text messages and a failed video chat. I win!

00:10:44:030000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:44:030000.Dialogue: So, what are we going to tell them?

00:10:46:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:46:210000.Dialogue: I'd like to tell them things are going well.

00:10:49:170000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:49:170000.Dialogue: Me, too. But before we get their hopes up, we should probably make sure we're on the same page.

00:10:54:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:10:54:230000.Dialogue: Okay. What page are you on?

00:10:59:070000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:10:59:070000.Dialogue: I'm on the one where I'm under a lot of pressure from my parents to get married and settle down and have a family, and I'm going to do it so they don't find out I'm gay.

00:11:20:210000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:11:20:210000.Dialogue: I know a fake marriage isn't an honest way to live, but you of all people should know how difficult it is to come out in our culture.

00:11:30:030000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:11:30:030000.Dialogue: Well, there's a rumor back in New Delhi that you're-- how shall we say-- comfortable in a sari.

00:11:38:200000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:11:38:200000.Dialogue: Really? The chocolate lava cake, the little soaps in the bathroom, and I'm sorry, but you're wearing more perfume than I am.

00:11:45:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:45:170000.Dialogue: That's Unbreakable by Khloe and Lamar.

00:11:50:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:50:040000.Dialogue: And for your information, it's unisex.

00:11:52:210000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:11:52:210000.Dialogue: Fill in the blank. I love the nightlife...

00:11:58:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:58:200000.Dialogue: With women! I like to boogie with women!

00:12:02:110000.Speaker: Lakshmi
00:12:02:110000.Dialogue: That's disappointing. You were exactly the kind of phony-baloney husband I was looking for.

00:12:08:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:08:160000.Dialogue: Thank you. And once again, my baloney likes girls.

00:12:14:080000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:12:14:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:12:14:080000.Dialogue: W-W-Wait! You don't want to put a bite of that in your mouth without trying my homemade Chantilly cream. Yeah, okay, that time I heard it.

00:12:37:060000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:12:37:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:37:060000.Dialogue: Oh, dear. Two suns and no sunscreen.

00:12:48:150000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:12:48:150000.Speaker: Spock

00:12:52:020000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:12:52:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:52:020000.Dialogue: What is it now, Tiny Spock?

00:12:55:020000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:12:55:020000.Speaker: Spock
00:12:55:020000.Dialogue: I am very disappointed in you. You broke your toy and switched it with Leonard's. You should be ashamed of yourself.

00:13:02:030000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:02:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:02:030000.Dialogue: You're the one who told me to play with it.

00:13:04:210000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:04:210000.Speaker: Spock
00:13:04:210000.Dialogue: If I told you to jump off the bridge of the Enterprise, would you do it?

00:13:08:150000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:08:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:08:150000.Dialogue: Oh, if I got on the bridge of the Enterprise, I would never, ever leave.

00:13:14:030000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:14:030000.Speaker: Spock
00:13:14:030000.Dialogue: Trust me, it gets old after a while.

00:13:19:190000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:19:190000.Speaker: Spock
00:13:19:190000.Dialogue: You must right your wrongs, Sheldon.

00:13:21:190000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:21:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:21:190000.Dialogue: Why? I got away with it. Leonard has his toy, and he's never going to open it, so he won't know it's broken. And I have a toy that isn't broken. Everybody's happy.

00:13:32:170000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:32:170000.Speaker: Spock

00:13:34:110000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:34:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:34:110000.Dialogue: I thought where you come from they don't have emotions.

00:13:37:100000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:37:100000.Speaker: Spock
00:13:37:100000.Dialogue: I come from a factory in Taiwan.

00:13:42:210000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:42:210000.Speaker: Spock

00:13:44:110000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:44:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:44:110000.Dialogue: You know what you are? Well, you're a green-blooded buzz kill.

00:13:49:070000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:49:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:49:070000.Dialogue: Perhaps it's time you beam on out of here.

00:13:51:190000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:51:190000.Speaker: Spock
00:13:51:190000.Dialogue: Fine. I will just use the transporter. Oh, right. You broke it.

00:13:58:140000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:13:58:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:58:140000.Dialogue: Very well. Cooper to Enterprise, one to beam up. Energize.

00:14:17:040000.Scene: Sheldon’s bedroom. Sheldon writhes in bed, then wakes up on an alien planet.
00:14:17:040000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:14:24:220000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:24:220000.Speaker: Raj

00:14:26:080000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:26:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:26:080000.Dialogue: Yeah, one sec. Oh, good. Ma would've killed me if she found out I broke my retainer.

00:14:34:190000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:34:190000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:34:190000.Dialogue: Hey, uh... can I run something by you? It's about Lakshmi.

00:14:38:160000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:38:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:38:160000.Dialogue: Yeah, sure. How are things going?

00:14:40:130000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:40:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:40:130000.Dialogue: We hit a couple of bumps. She lives over in Manhattan Beach, so it takes, like, an hour to get there. And she's a lesbian.

00:14:48:020000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:48:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:48:020000.Dialogue: What do you mean, she's a lesbian?

00:14:51:050000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:14:51:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:51:050000.Dialogue: Well, you know how whenever you and I would try to hit on women in bars and they'd blow us off and then we'd tell each other they were probably gay? It's like that. Except this time, it's true.

00:15:02:000000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:02:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:02:000000.Dialogue: Then why did she even go out with you?

00:15:04:080000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:04:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:04:080000.Dialogue: She was looking for a husband so she can appear to be straight. And, you know, it sounded crazy to me at first... but I'm actually thinking about doing it.

00:15:15:010000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:15:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:15:010000.Dialogue: Okay, so the reason that might sound crazy... is 'cause it's crazy!

00:15:20:220000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:20:220000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:20:220000.Dialogue: Look, Howard, you're in a relationship. You know you have to make compromises.

00:15:25:100000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:25:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:25:100000.Dialogue: Yes, but my compromises are about which bedspread to buy or whose turn it is to do the laundry, Bernadette's or my mom's.

00:15:36:080000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:36:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:36:080000.Dialogue: It's a great deal. We both get our parents off our backs, I don't have to come home to an empty apartment every night. Plus, once I'm married, I can finally eat carbs again and let myself go.

00:15:47:140000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:47:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:47:140000.Dialogue: Why don't you tell your parents you want to try to find someone else? Maybe one who hasn't slept with more woman than you.

00:15:55:080000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:15:55:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:55:080000.Dialogue: Because this one wants to marry me. I might never find another one who does.

00:16:00:220000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:16:00:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:00:220000.Dialogue: So you're seriously thinking about marrying someone you're never gonna have sex with?

00:16:05:020000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:16:05:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:05:020000.Dialogue: I can't believe your attitude. I thought you were in favor of gay people getting married.

00:16:11:140000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:16:11:140000.Speaker: Howard

00:16:13:210000.Scene: Howard’s laboratory. Howard is soldering something.
00:16:13:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:13:210000.Dialogue: Do you hear how homophobic you sound?

00:16:58:080000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:16:58:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:58:080000.Dialogue: Oh, I don't want a broken toy.

00:17:04:060000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:17:04:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:07:040000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:17:07:040000.Speaker: Leonard

00:17:08:160000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:17:08:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:10:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:17:10:210000.Speaker: Penny

00:17:11:210000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is working on his laptop. Spock is looking at him judgementally. He switches the two toys.
00:17:11:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:11:210000.Dialogue: Really? I don't even notice anymore.
